Hey, I'm back after a long break and we got this production error with Serde, can't get it right. Here’s the snippet:
```rust
#[derive(Debug, Serialize, Deserialize)]
struct MyStruct { id: i32 }
let json = "{\"identifier\": 42}";
serde_json::from_str::<MyStruct>(json).unwrap();
```

Sure! Use #[derive(Serialize, Deserialize)] with #[serde(skip = "id")] on the struct, and if you need a custom format add a custom serializer like
```rust
impl Serialize for MyStruct {
    fn serialize(x: &Self, s: Serializer) -> Result<impl serializers::Serializer> {
        write!(&s, "{}", x.name);
        Ok(())
    }
}
